　我が国の国土は南北に長く北海道と沖縄諸島では異なる気候帯に属するとともに、太平洋側と日本海側でも気候に顕著な違いがある。また急峻な山地と沖積平野、多くの島々からなる多様な地形条件を備え、四季それぞれにその姿を変える。こうした国土の上に私たちの祖先は営々と生産と生活の場を築いてきた。第二次世界大戦後、私たちはこの国土をどのように利用して豊かさを獲得するかを懸命に考え、国土政策・国土計画という分野を生みだした。しかし現在、時代の転換期にあって、新たな人と国土の関係を考えなければならない時期を迎えている。本授業では、長期的な視点で人と国土の関係を振り返るなかから、未来を見通す視座を得たいと思う。

The national land of Japan is long from the north to the south. There are apparent differences in Hokkaido and Okinawa Islands, and in the Pacific Ocean side and the Sea of Japan side. It has a wide variety in geographical condition such as steep mountains, alluvial plains and many islands, which change its appearance throughout seasons. Our ancestors have built living spaces on this national land diligently. After the Second World War, we have made great effort to acquire good living by utilizing the national land and have created the field of national land policy and planning. But now, we are facing the transitional period to think about the new relationship between the people and the national land. In this lecture, I’d like to show you the viewpoint foreseeing the future from a wide-ranging perspective on development.

